Cumulated content of eFulfilment meetings

Working Group meeting 30/03/2023

Date: 30/03/2023
Participants:, Natalie Muric, Peter Borresen
Model editor: Andreea PasÄƒre
Note editor: Jana Ahmad

Agenda

  • Discuss the eFulfilment model with respect to the CEN-TC-440-Peppol-Despatch advice model:

    • To continue from Delivery Term

Discussion

The WG compared the CEN-TC-440-Peppol-Despatch advice model with our eFulfilment model and made changes accordingly, as follows.

  • To cover Handling instructions: epo-ful:hasHandlingInstruction is added between at-voc-new:handling-instructionis and epo-ful:TransportHandlingUnit

  • Transport equipment, Handling unit hazardous indicator, Shipping marks are covered in eFulfillment model.

  • epo-ful:fullness-indicator code is deleted

  • The usefulness of the data type property epo-ful:isReturnable needs to be evaluated.

  • It was noted that Returnable Item need to be discussed

  • To cover Packaging type code: epo-ful:Packaging-type code is added with epo-ful:hasPackagingType relation to epo-ful:package.

  • Minimum temperature, Measurement dimension, Maximum temperature: are covered in eFulfilment.

  • Goods item:

    • Identifier for epo-ful:GoodsItem is covered

    • Hazardous risk indicator is covered.

  • epo-ful:isHazardousRisk is removed from epo-ful:TransportHandlingUnit

  • Quantity for Goods Iem:

    • epo-ful:hasTotalPackageQuantity is deleted.

    • Quantity is covered by epo-ful:hasTotalGoodsItemQuantity

  • Dispatch line note

    • It is covered by dct:description in epo-cat:Line

  • epo:hasNodespatcheableQuantity Relation is deleted

  • For Document reference

    • epo-ful:hasAssociatedDocument is added to epo-ful:DepatchLine

  • Item information: is covered.

  • Good item definition with additional information are added.

  • Certificate: is covered

Working Group meeting 24/03/2023

Date: 24/03/2023
Participants:, Natalie Muric, Peter Borresen
Model editor: Andreea PasÄƒre
Note editor: Jana Ahmad

Agenda

  • Discuss the eFulfilment model with respect to the CEN-TC-440-Peppol-Despatch advice model

    • To continue from Consignee information.

Discussion

The eFulfilment model was discussed and compared with the CEN-TC-440-Peppol-Despatch advice model in order to identify any differences or areas for improvement. Several changes were made to the eFulfilment model to align it with the Peppol standard, as follows.

All parties and roles are covered in eFulfilment model * Shipment information: is covered in eFulfilment model

  • For Consignment information in Peppol requirements:

    • Handling code: a listcode is created

    • Handling Instruction and identifier are covered in eFulfilment model

  • The "dct:Description" property has been added to "epo-ful:ShipmentAgreement" to cover shipment description requirements.

  • Good Item: Declared statistics value amount

  • The property TransportHandlingUnit is deleted from dispatch identifier class

  • Carrier in Peppol requirement

    • Carrier party is covered i eFulfilment model in the level of consignee, epo-ful:ShipmentStage uses epo-ful:TransportMeans which has a driver person epo-ful:TransportMeansOperator.

  • Driver identification document type:

    • Epo:hasDocumenttype property is added

  • eop-ful:hasOperatorLicienceId relation is added

    • For Transport mode code, Transport means type code requirements.

  • transport mode is covered by epo-ful:transport-mode

  • At-voc-new:transport-means codelist is added

  • epo-hasOperatorLicenceID association is added.

  • For Train identifier requirement:

    • transport means id is updated with identifier;

  • Delivery information and Delivery term location: are covered in eFulfilment model

  • epo-ord:specifiesPlaceOfStorage is deleted.

  • epo-ord:concernsPlaceOfDelivery is changed to epo-ord:specifiesPlaceOfDelivery

  • Delivery tracking identifier and period:

    • In ePo, there are hasTrackingId, deliveryPeriod properties

  • Delivery location

    • In ePo, there is dct:Location.

  • Estimated delivery period requirement:

    • epo-ful:hasEstimatedDeliveryPeriod in epo-ful:Shipmentinformation level

  • Actual or expected despatch period requirement:

    • epo-ful:dispatchDate

  • Despatch address requirement

    • epo-ord:specifiesPlaceOfStorage is removed and replaced with epo-ful:specifiesPlacesofDespatch.

    • During the discussion, it was pointed out that the concept of a virtual location may be necessary in cases where the order pertains to a service rather than a physical product.

Working Group meeting 14/03/2023

Date: 14/03/2023
Participants: Natalie Muric, Najeh Hajlaoui, Ivan Willer, Peter Borresen, Paloma Arillo
Model editor: Andreea PasÄƒre
Note editor: Jana Ahmad

Agenda

  • Continue discussing eFulfillment

    • To continue from: ConsolidatedShipment (from the spreadsheet)

  • A party should have an authorization. This needs to be modelled.

  • Know how to integrate Certificate

Discussion

WG checked if the ePO model is complete regarding UBL eFulfilment requirements by having diagrams which clearly depict the necessary elements, as following:

  • Document identifier

    • epo-ful: DespatchAdviceDocument object is created, and it announces epo-ful:DespatchAdvice

  • Despatch advice status code:

    • at-voc-new:fulfilment-document-status and at-voc-new:document-type enumerations are created

  • Despatch advice Type code:

    • at-voc-new:despatch-advice-type enumeration is created

  • epo-cat:Catalogue id defined: A list describing a set of items offered for purchase that can be processed in an electronic way.

  • epo-ful: DespatchAdviceDocument is defined : A document used to describe the despatch or delivery of goods, services or work

  • Depatch note:

    • epo:hasAdditionalInformation for epo-ful:DespatchAdvice (epo-cat:PostAwardObject)

  • Order reference:

    • epo-ful:DesparchAdvice refers to epo-ord:order

  • Additional Order reference

    • epo-ful:hasAssociatedDocument

  • Document Type:

    • dct:description property is added to epo:Document

  • Attachment:

    • epo:hasAccessURL

  • Party name:

    • Despatch role class

  • Despatch party electronic address

    • epo:Channel

  • Tax scheme:

    • epo:hasTaxIdentifier property

  • Despatch party name

    • Organization has a name.

Actions:

  • Embedded binary object

    • Note: binary objects need to be discussed, find a way to map things that we can not do from PEPPOL, epo-ontology, etc.

  • Despatch Roles class is created:

  • epo-ful:ShipmentAgreement object is created and epo-ful:Shipment is removed

  • epo-ful:specifiesDespatcher relation is created between epo-ful:DespatchAdvice and epo-ful:Despatcher

  • epo-ful:refersToConsignment relation is created between epo-ful:DespatchAdvice and epo-ful:Consignment

Working Group meeting 02/03/2023

Date: 02/03/2023
Participants:, Natalie Muric, Peter Borresen, Christian Mondini
Model editor: Andreea PasÄƒre
Note editor: Jana Ahmad

Agenda

  • Discuss the eFulfilment model

  • Discuss shipping mark

  • Discuss the concept of ReceivedAdvice

Discussion

The attribute "epo-ful:hasShippingMark" is present in both "epo-ful:TransportHandlingUnit" and "epo-ord:DeliveryInformation", leading to duplicated information. The working group has decided to keep it as is for now and further discuss it in the future.

The implementation of ReceivedAdvice will be postponed until we finish with DespatchAdvice.

The WG compared the CEN-TC-440-Peppol-Despatch advice model with our eFulfilment model and made changes accordingly, as follows.

  • epo-ful:hasAllowanceChargeReason relation is added to epo-cat:ChargInformation

  • The property 'epo-ful:hasBaseAmount' is added to the 'MonetaryValue' class to enable the use of base amount in eFulfilment.

  • A new relationship, epo-ful:hasAttachmentDocument, has been created to fulfill the requirement for an External Reference.

    • It needs to be checked how the (cac:AdditionalDocumentReference) is modeled in the Order module.

  • epo-ful:hasCarrierConsingnmentId has been added to epo-ful:Consignment

  • epo-ful:hasSpecialServiceInstructions has been added

  • epo-ful:NetWeightMeasure and ChargeableWeightMeasure have been added

  • epo-ful:hasConsignmentDeclaredStatisticsValue has been added

eFulfilment meeting 11/08/2022

Date: 11/08/2022
Participants: Veit Jahns, Natalie Muric, Giovanni Paolo Sellitto
Model editor: Eugeniu Costetchi
Note editor: Andreea PasÄƒre

Discussion

Discuss the Roles structure from PEPPOL Despatch Advice

  • In PEPPOL, the roles are split into parties like:

    • Customer

    • Supplier

    • Carrier

  • In ePO Supplier and Carrier are classes that go on the Economic Operator side, while Customer goes on the Buyer side.

  • Buyer and Customer should be at the same level in the ePO.

  • In UBL, whenever we have a â€œpartyâ€ we map to Organisation.

  • We should find a gathering concept for all the roles on the buyer (procurer) side and another gathering concept for the economic operator (seller) side.

  • In the post-award phase, the Buyer becomes the Customer and the Winner becomes the Supplier.

  • Using the term â€œpartyâ€ for concepts in ePO will be too confusing with UBL.

  • The definition of party from UBL is: â€œParty:
    A class to describe an organisation, sub-organization, or individual fulfilling a role in a business process.â€

  • We can have a PurchasingActor and a SupplingActor.

  • The customer definition does not fit for ProcurementServiceProvider.

  • Supplier for pre-award phase does not work.

  • This does not fit well, so Customer, Supplier and Carrier will be removed for the time being.

  • Buyer and Consignee are parties in UBL and in ePo they are roles.

  • Conceptually, parties are some kind of role.

  • Discussing the Buyer roles dependencies:

  • You have to award in order to be able to sign.

  • Originator has two different definitions in PEPPOL:

    • From despatch: The party who will eventually receive and consume the goods and on whose behalf the buyer makes the purchase.

    • From ordering: A person or unit that initiates an order.

  • Adding a new responsibility for the Buyer role:

    • In Ordering: A person or unit that initiates an order.

    • In Fulfilment: The party who will eventually receive and consume the goods and on whose behalf the buyer makes the purchase.

  • New roles might need to be added:

    • Procedure awarder

    • Procedure initiator

  • Getting the roles from ePO frozen version 2.0.2.

  • Synchronise definitions and names for roles concepts.

  • Deliveree and Consignee are similar in Despatch.

  • Decided to change the namespaces so we can differentiate between roles in different PEPPOL diagrams:

Consignee versus Deliveree

  • The different definitions of Consignee from PEPPOL Ordering and PEPPOL Despatch Advice are discussed.

    • This is compared with the epo:Deliveree from frozen 2.0.2 definition.

  • Created an ePO issue GH 367:

    • Updating the definition to epo-ord:Deliveree.

    • epo-ord:Deliveree to be equivalent to both the roles of Consignee in PEPPOL ordering and in PEPPOL despatch advice, both of which have different definitions. ==== Originator

  • We have 3 different definitions:

    • PEPPOL ordering: â€œA person or unit that initiates an order.â€

    • PEPPOL despatch adviceâ€ â€œThe party who will eventually receive and consume the goods and on whose behalf the buyer makes the purchase.â€

    • ePO Ordering â€œA role of an agent that expresses the needs to trigger the procurement.
      Additional Information:
      The originator is often the end-user.â€

  • Triggering an order does not mean that it will receive it as well.

  • Proposed concepts to be discussed in the following meeting:

  • Created an ePO issue GH 368.
